, "annotation_id": "QQ_106"}, {"decision": "Check your blood glucose four times daily (prior to breakfast, lunch, dinner, and at night before bed).  ", "category": "Category 2: Gathering additional information", "start_offset": 9149, "end_offset": 9254, "annotation_id": "QQ_107"}, {"decision": ").  You are starting a new medicine for diabetes.  ", "category": "Category 5: Drug related", "start_offset": 9250, "end_offset": 9301, "annotation_id": "QQ_108"}, {"decision": "If your blood sugar remains very high then you should call your primary care doctor to discuss initiating the insulin", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 9301, "end_offset": 9418, "annotation_id": "QQ_109"}, {"decision": "Vac changes ", "category": "Category 6: Therapeutic procedure related", "start_offset": 9422, "end_offset": 9434, "annotation_id": "QQ_110"}, {"decision": "Vac changes per VNA with pre-medication", "category": "Category 5: Drug related", "start_offset": 9422, "end_offset": 9461, "annotation_id": "QQ_111"}, {"decision": "Activity:  Regular walking encouraged", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 9464, "end_offset": 9501, "annotation_id": "QQ_112"}, {"decision": "Diet:  low sodium, low fat, and low protein encouraged", "category": "Category 6: Therapeutic procedure related", "start_offset": 9504, "end_offset": 9558, "annotation_id": "QQ_113"}, {"decision": "YOU ARE AT VERY HIGH RISK TO DEVELOP LONG TERM DEVASTATING IRREVERSIBLE KIDNEY PROBLEMS*****  THE GOOD NEWS IS THAT THESE PROBLEMS HAVE NOT FULLY DEVELOPED!  ", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 9565, "end_offset": 9723, "annotation_id": "QQ_114"}, {"decision": "A LOW SODIUM DIET,", "category": "Category 6: Therapeutic procedure related", "start_offset": 9752, "end_offset": 9770, "annotation_id": "QQ_115"}, {"decision": "YOU MUST LOSE WEIGHT, FOLLOW A LOW SODIUM DIET, GET YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE (VIA DIET, WEIGHT LOSS, EXERCISE, AND MEDICINES) UNDER BETTER CONTROL, AND CONTROL YOUR DIABETES OR YOU WILL SUFFER THE DEVASTATING CONSEQUENCES OF KIDNEY FAILURE.", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 9723, "end_offset": 9958, "annotation_id": "QQ_116"}, {"decision": "Please call your doctor or return to the emergency room if you have any of the following:  * Increased redness, swelling, and/or pain at your wound, or foul-smelling drainage from your wound * You experience new chest pain, pressure, squeezing or tightness. * New or worsening cough or wheezing. * If you are vomiting and cannot keep in fluids or your medications. * You are getting dehydrated due to continued vomiting, diarrhea  or other reasons. Signs of dehydration include dry mouth, rapid heartbeat or feeling dizzy or faint when standing. * You see blood or dark/black material when you vomit or have a bowel movement. * You have shaking chills, or a fever greater than 101.5 (F) degrees or 38(C) degrees. * Any serious change in your symptoms, or any new symptoms that concern you.", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 9960, "end_offset": 10749, "annotation_id": "QQ_117"}, {"decision": "* You are getting dehydrated due to continued vomiting, diarrhea  or other reasons. Signs of dehydration include dry mouth, rapid heartbeat or feeling dizzy or faint when standing. * You see blood or dark/black material when you vomit or have a bowel movement. * You have shaking chills, or a fever greater than 101.5 (F) degrees or 38(C) degrees. * Any serious change in your symptoms, or any new symptoms that concern you.", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 10325, "end_offset": 10749, "annotation_id": "QQ_118"}, {"decision": "1.  Dr. [**First Name (STitle) **]:  Follow-up in three weeks.  Please call her office at [**Telephone/Fax (1) 39468**] to schedule a follow-up appointment.", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": 10775, "end_offset": 10931, "annotation_i